Parliament, Sunday, 5 July 2020 – The Chairperson of the Portfolio Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs, Ms Faith Muthambi, will tomorrow embark on a Covid-19 oversight programme in her Capricorn District Municipality constituency in Limpopo Province.
	
	She will receive briefings on the provision of water, distribution of food parcels and hand sanitisers and the role and functions of the local coronavirus command centres from Capricorn District Municipality, Provincial Department of Cooperative Governance, Human Settlements and Traditional Affairs, Provincial Department of Water Affairs, Lepelle Water Board and National Department of Cooperative Governance.
	
	Details of the oversight visit:
	Date : Monday, 6 July 2020
	Venue: Polokwane Local Municipality
	Time: 10:00 – 16:00
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON COOPERATIVE GOVERNANCE AND TRADITIONAL AFFAIRS, MS FAITH MUTHAMBI.
	
	For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer:
